# HairMNL theme — guards for offload-dispatched agents

This file is read by OpenCode and Cursor agents dispatched on bd-tracked
tasks. The rules below are NON-NEGOTIABLE for any RW work in this repo.
They are project-specific overrides that supplement (never weaken) the
global skill SOPs in `~/.claude/skills/offload.md` and
`~/.claude/skills/cursor-offload.md`.

## Hard locks — agent must NOT do any of these

1. **No `shopify theme push`** — coordinator owns all theme deploys per
   the push protocol in `CLAUDE.md`. The 2026-04-26 regression history
   is what this guard prevents. Stage with `git add` only.
2. **No `git push` to remote** — coordinator owns commit + push. Agents
   may stage and locally commit only if explicitly instructed; otherwise
   stage only.
3. **No `bd close <id>`** — coordinator runs merge-gate (lint + diff +
   draft + smoke + live + commit + push) and closes after live
   verification. Agents may `bd update --append-notes "..."` for
   progress, but never close. (This overrides Cursor's default
   self-close behavior for this project.)
4. **No edits to admin-managed files**:
   - `templates/*.json`
   - `config/settings_data.json`
   - `config/settings_schema.json`
   - These are auto-edited by the Shopify Theme Editor. Local edits
     get clobbered. If a task seems to require a settings change,
     STOP and surface it to the coordinator.
5. **No edits to `assets/theme.css`** — that file is minified output
   (~50K lines). For style overrides, edit `snippets/css-overrides.liquid`
   instead. Each existing override has a `/* CLS fix YYYY-MM-DD <bd-id>
   — <reason> */` comment block; follow that convention.
6. **No `git add .` / `git add -A`** — only stage explicit paths the
   bd issue's design lists. Concurrent dispatches might leave stray
   working-tree artifacts in `.claude/`, `.codex/`, etc.
7. **No copy paraphrasing** — product titles, blog body content, store
   strings stay verbatim unless the bd issue's design says otherwise.

## Source ↔ minified mirror discipline (`assets/theme.dev.js` ↔ `assets/theme.js`)

The theme has TWO JS files:
- `assets/theme.dev.js` — readable source (with comments + spaces).
- `assets/theme.js` — minified production version. **This is what
  actually runs.**

Any change in one MUST be mirrored in the other. The minified mirror
is fragile (single-letter variable names, comma operators, no comments)
— if you can't reliably hand-edit it, surface to the coordinator. The
`gjv` and `o0z` issues both shipped paired edits to these files.

## Don't rename — GTM and dashboard depend on these

These names are referenced from GTM tags, the dashboard's GA4 query,
and external tools. Don't rename without coordinating a GTM container
update + dashboard query update.

| Name | Where | Consumer |
|---|---|---|
| `theme:cart:change` | dispatched in CartItems.fireChange | header cart count, drawer, BOGOS, LimeSpot |
| `hairmnl_js_error` | dataLayer push from window.error handler | GTM tag 776 → GA4 |
| `error_type` / `error_message` / `error_source` | dataLayer keys for hairmnl_js_error | GA4 custom dimensions |
| `template` (Liquid global) | dataLayer key in web-vitals reporter | GA4 custom dimension `template` (for per-template CWV slicing) |

## Don't rename — DOM hooks

CSS rules + JS selectors point at these. Renaming breaks both.

| Selector / data-attr | Used by |
|---|---|
| `data-section-id`, `data-block-id`, `data-section-type` | Shopify section system |
| `[data-cart-item]`, `[data-cart-form]`, `[data-cart-loading]` | CartItems class + cart drawer |
| `[data-header-wrapper]`, `data-header-height`, `data-header-sticky` | Header init + sticky scroll |
| `header.theme__header`, `.header__wrapper` | Header CSS + the kt0 `contain:layout` fix |
| `[data-api-content]` | Section-rendering API (cart bulk-sections POST) |

## CSS custom properties — use existing tokens

The theme defines its CSS custom properties in `assets/theme.css`'s
`:root` block. Before adding any `var(--…)` reference, verify the
token exists. Common existing tokens:
- `--color-text`, `--color-bg`, `--color-accent`
- `--font-base`, `--font-heading`, `--font-accent`
- `--header-height-tablet`, `--header-height-desktop`

If a needed token doesn't exist, define it via
`snippets/css-variables.liquid` (existing pattern) — NOT by adding to
`assets/theme.css`.

## Push protocol (when coordinator deploys)

For reference — agents don't push, but the coordinator does:

1. `git diff HEAD <file>` — confirm exact intended hunks.
2. `shopify theme push --theme=140785582179 --nodelete --only=<file>` — draft first.
3. Smoke test on draft preview URL `?preview_theme_id=140785582179`.
4. `shopify theme push --theme=131664707683 --allow-live --only=<file>` — live.
5. `git add <file>; git commit -m "..."; git pull --rebase; git push`.
6. `bd update <id> --append-notes "MERGE_GATE_PASS at <ts>\n$(git show HEAD --stat)"`.
7. `bd close <id>`.

